12/06/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Some 27 Americans were injured as their bus, heading to a Catholic shrine in southern BiH, collided with another vehicle Monday (June 11th), some 20km south of Sarajevo.
The US Embassy said most of the passengers are from Milwaukee,Wisconsin and were on a ten-day trip that included a visit to the famous shrine in Medjugorje.
(AP, BBC, Xinhua, RTRS - 11/06/07)
